review_blob: Rich fruity aroma with a deeper crystal gold color, though the taste was a little off, with a bit of sourness lasting right into the aftertaste.  May have just been a bad bottle, since I generally like this beer.
Light and pleasant aroma with a sharp crystal yellow color.  Flavor was clean and fruity with a sharp degree of carbonation.  Left a long sweet finish.
Pretty color, that of burnt umber.  A lot of caramel on this one mostly on the long finish, though it was also present on the initial flavoring.  Did not taste the strawberry though.
Pretty light amber color.  Flavor of pine, which I like.  A good tasting beer that would be hard for me to drink more than one or two.  Good body with a log long finish.
Richer shade of gold than comparable brews in this genre.  Light body but a slightly sweeter flavor than I was expecting gave it a better more rounded flavor and a longer time on the palate.
Light and fruity flavor.  Pale gold for color.  Not extraordinary but plain and drinkable.  Average.
Pale gold in color.  Nice easy drinking brew, somewhat light on the body but not undrinkable, just basic and pleasant.
This one I tasted in a blind beer tasting and thought it was a little odd.  Tasted more like a very fruity soda than like a beer.  Lighter gold in color.
I liked this beer, though it did have a bit of a hard bite with some acidic tendencies and was a little too fizzy.  Bright gold color.

I love this beer.  It has a color of dark chocolate along with a coffee/chocolate aroma.  Not bitter at all, in fact it has a touch of sweetness that leaves a lingering taste of cocoa powder on the palate.  Just delightful.
Beautiful burnt orange color.  All I really tasted on this was bitterness, no hops or anything, just bitterness.  Sort of middle of the road.
Very much of a flavor of burnt apples, or similar kitchen smells and tastes.  Not very appealing other than its color.

This pairs very well with food.  Sometimes it is a bit light, but is still a solid brew for those hot summer days primarily due to its clean finish.  It has a lovely gold color, that pours with not too much head and has a pleasant aroma.

Very disappointed in this effort.  Aroma had sort of a stale scent that reminded me of the next morning.  It also was not as murky as most of this style.  There are better hefeweizens and better Sam Adams to spend your money on.
Had a strong taste like cherry flavored bubblegum, though I did like the color.  A good starter beer for a novice.
Love the color and aroma but baking spice flavors are overpowering. And the finish clashes with the rest of the taste, a very harsh bitter taste.
has an upfront sweetness and sour finish that lasts and lasts. Not  an appealing brew.
beer_name: Blue Moon Honey Moon Summer Ale

review_blob: Nice pale gold color. Good medium body fairly clean finish. Pairs well with food, especially chicken.
Like the amber color, but too sweet and too long on the finish. Not an easy drinker.
Light in color for an oktoberfest it seems. Drinkable, but bitter. Probably better with food.
Vegetal, almost squash like aroma that follows thru to the flavor.  wish it had a cleaner finish. Like it, but couldnt drink more than one.
